         <particDesc>
            <listPerson>
               <person>
                  <persName role="owner" ref="PRS0000">The name of the original donor has been erased. The name of Za-Manfas Qǝddus (the baptismal name of däǧǧazmač Säbagadis), as well as of his father Walda Lǝʿul and mother Walatta Ṣǝyon, is written in the main or secondary hand, in the supplication formulas over the erasures (e.g., <locus target="2rb">2rb</locus>, 3rbc, 5vc, 6ra; s. also <locus target="63rc">63rc</locus>). The name Säbagadǝs is mentioned on <locus target="117vc">117vc</locus>. &#xD;
On <locus target="46vc">46vc</locus> and 109ra, the partly erased name of the original donor can be reconstructed as Ḫayla Śǝllāse. The name of his mother begins as Walatta Nǝ- (perhaps Walatta Nǝgǝśt, cf. especially <locus target="179ra">179ra</locus>). The name of his father may be tentatively reconstructed as Takla Hāymānot.</persName>
